This equipment uses the Aurora system as a base.

================================================================================
2. MODS .................................................................[MOD]
================================================================================
--- Mod 1. Start From Internal/External Input ---

The equipment includes an option to choose if the start command is provided by 
an operator (internal, via touchscreen), or an external input. The external 
command is a relay.

--- Mod 2. Include/Exclude Calendar ---

The equipment includes an option to choose if the calendar is used to control
the sanitization cycles (date/time) or not (continuous ozone production).

--- Mod 3. Ozone Sensor Control ---

The equipment includes a remote ozone sensor to read or control ozone 
production. The read/control selection is chosen via touch screen.

--- Mod 4. Ozone Sensor Alarm ---

The equipment includes an integrated ozone sensor for alarm. The ozone alarm 
value is set from the touch screen. The the alarm value is reached, ozone 
production is alted.

--- Mod 5. Alarm Screen---

The equipment includes an alarm screen (touch screen) that shows when the
ozone alarm value is reached. The operator must unlock this screen manually
by selecting the "re-enable" option in this screen.

